<subSubSection id="C36696BB8E53FFBEFF1AFD15D8FEFC37" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3C5308E53FFBEFF1AFD15D8FEFC37" blockId="8.[163,1070,750,977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">
Comment: 
<location id="8EA393EB8E53FFBEFEF6FD15D80BFCE2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D574268E53FFBEFF1AFDA5D8FEFC37:8EA393EB8E53FFBEFEF6FD15D80BFCE2" box="[335,374,750,772]" country="Iceland" name="The" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">The</location>
original description is based on 
<specimenCount id="9D7A0EB98E53FFBEFD6BFD14DA3BFCE2" box="[722,838,750,772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54C77B928E53FFBEFCE9FD14DAD4FCE2" box="[848,937,751,772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">syntypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Wadi 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E53FFBEFF1AFCF7D9B7FCC4" box="[163,202,780,802]" name="Iceland" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Isla</collectingCountry>
, 
<date id="FFC2E3F08E53FFBEFF6CFCF7D846FCC4" box="[213,315,780,802]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" value="1933-02-28">
<collectingDate id="EF861A188E53FFBEFF6CFCF7D846FCC4" box="[213,315,780,802]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" value="1933-02-28">28.2.1933</collectingDate>
</date>
(Süd-Sinai)&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E53FFBEFE76FCF7DB36FCC4" author="KOCH C" box="[463,587,780,802]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" pagination="33 - 91" refId="ref7632" refString="KOCH C. (1934): Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der entomologischen Expeditionen seiner Durchlaucht des Fuersten Alessandro C. della Torre e Tasso nach Aegypten und auf die Halbinsel Sinai. IV. Staphylinidae (Coleoptera). - Bulletin de la Societe Royale Entomologique d'Egypte 1934: 33 - 91." type="journal article" year="1934">
<specimenCode id="DBDA6D4B8E53FFBEFE76FCF7DB36FCC4" box="[463,587,780,802]" collectionCode="KOCH" country="Japan" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13442" name="Kochi University" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" type="Herbarium">KOCH 1934</specimenCode>
</bibRefCitation>
). One of the type specimens was located in the Frey collection, which is currently housed in the 
<collectionCode id="ED6D5DF58E53FFBEFD10FCD1DB85FCD9" box="[681,760,810,831]" country="0" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/1d5a-4efs" name="Natural History Museum Bucharest" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">NHMB</collectionCode>
. This species is characterized particularly by its large size (total length 
<quantity id="4C8468D58E53FFBEFDD9FCBDDBC9FCBA" box="[608,692,838,860]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4C8468D58E53FFBEFC28FCBDDA9BFCBA" box="[913,998,838,860]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
), palereddish coloration, long and slender antennae (
<quantity id="4C8468D58E53FFBEFD30FC98DBA7FC9F" box="[649,730,867,889]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
) with distinctly oblong antennomeres I-IX, and by the dense and coarse punctation of the whole body, particularly of the abdomen. The habitus, the forebody, and the abdomen of the examined 
<typeStatus id="54C77B928E53FFBEFC0DFC64DD7EFC52" box="[948,1027,927,948]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">syntype</typeStatus>
are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="1347D9B58E53FFBEFE90FC40D802FC37" box="[297,383,955,977]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="6.[163,203,1403,1423]" captionTargetBox="[176,1060,209,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-0@6.[171,1060,209,1395]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 1-8: Pinophilinus spinosus nov.sp. (1-5) and P. schatzmayri (KOCH) (6-8): (1, 6) habitus; (2, 7) forebody; (3, 8) abdomen; (4) male sternite VIII; (5) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-3, 6-8: 1.0 mm; 4-5: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341016/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Figs 6-8</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
